fields.description:
"BlockVerificationFailures" and "BlocksVerified" show up as 0 in Datanode JMX
Looking at the code, i see below description.
{noformat}
`BlockVerificationFailures` | Total number of verifications failures | 
`BlocksVerified` | Total number of blocks verified | 
{noformat}

comments.body:
Test failures are not related. They either pass when ran locally or are known issues. E.g. HDFS-12480 is addressing TestNameNodeMetrics.

The block verification failure count was intended for actual checksum errors. I don't think we need to increment the failure count here.  Other than that, the patch looks good.
{code}
    if (block == null) {
      metrics.incrBlockVerificationFailures();
      return -1; // block not found.
    }
{code}
